Loose Women panellist Brenda Edwards, 53, took to Instagram on Mother’s Day to share a series of photos featuring her late son, Jamal Edwards, who died last month aged just 31. The heartbroken mum posted a collage to her 103,000 which featured photos of Jamal and his sister Tanisha. READ MORE:Sally Nugent 'stopped in tracks' over BBC Breakfast admission  Celine echoed: “Thinking of you Brenda. Wonderful photos. Biggest hug.”Sonia added: “Hold on to your memories.”And Blue singer Duncan James shared six love heart emojis.Jamal, best known as the founder of SBTV, died unexpectedly in February. His platform helped launch the careers of Ed Sheeran, Jessie J and Dave.Jamal was also awarded an MBE in 2014 for his services to music. Brenda released a heartbreaking statement at the time of his death, which read: “It is with the deepest heartache that I confirm that my beautiful son Jamal Edwards passed away yesterday morning after a sudden illness.“Myself, his sister Tanisha and the rest of his family and friends are completely devastated. He was the centre of our world. DON'T MISSBBC Breakfast's Rachel Burden tells Naga Munchetty to 'get well soon'[LATEST]Craig Fairbrass on his journey from Hollywood to EastEnders[INSIGHT]Meghan Markle unlikely to 'get hands on any royal palaces'[NEWS] "I would like to thank everyone for their messages of love and support. Jamal was an inspiration to myself and so many."Our love for him lives on, his legacy lives on. Long live Jamal Edwards MBE, MBA, PHD.”